I have another question. Supposing I want to set a property called "color" for a particular widget. If there is already a method called `color()` - either defined by me or in the underlying tk object - I can't make a property with the same name, right? Is there any way of overriding this? 

For example, in the `Tk` object, there is a method called `title()` defined. This means I can't add something like 

```python
@property
    def title(self):
        return self.title()
```

... because I'm relying on the `title()` method to get me the title, but creating the property also called `title` creates an infinite recursion. 

So is it not possible to have `app.title = "Nice title"`, or is there a way of overriding this somehow. (At this stage, `App` extends `Tk`)

